title: The Prairie Traveler
creator: Randolph Barnes Marcy
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Prairie Traveler, by Randolph Barnes Marcy. Read by Angela Rowland. Commissioned by the US War Department and written in 1859 by a decorated US Army captain, The Prairie Traveler is a complete how-to travel guide for the westward-bound pioneer. Covering topics from first aid for rattlesnake bites to how to travel 70 miles across the desert without water for one's livestock, the guide includes 28 travel itineraries with mileage and firewood availability.
